.TH FLEET\-MANAGER 1 "2026-04-04" "machine-setup 2.0" "Machine Setup Manual"
.SH NAME
fleet\-manager.sh \- manage a fleet of machines for batch setup operations
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B fleet\-manager.sh
\fISUBCOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manages a fleet of machines registered in a local configuration file.
Supports registering, removing, listing, and running setup on individual
machines or the entire fleet in batch.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B register \fINAME\fR \fIHOST\fR [\fIPROFILE\fR]
Register a machine with the given name, SSH host, and optional profile.
.TP
.B remove \fINAME\fR
Remove a registered machine by name.
.TP
.B list
List all registered machines with their host and profile.
.TP
.B setup \fINAME\fR
Run machine-setup on the named machine via SSH.
.TP
.B setup\-all
Run machine-setup on all registered machines.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.machine\-setup/fleet.conf
Fleet configuration file storing registered machine entries.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error (unknown subcommand, missing machine, SSH failure).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Register a machine:
.B fleet\-manager.sh register webserver user@web.example.com full
.TP
List all machines:
.B fleet\-manager.sh list
.TP
Run setup on a single machine:
.B fleet\-manager.sh setup webserver
.TP
Run setup on all machines:
.B fleet\-manager.sh setup\-all
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR setup.sh (1),
.BR remote\-setup.sh (1)
.SH AUTHORS
Machine Setup contributors.
